{"key": "{\"messages\": [{\"content\": [{\"text\": \"Warmup\", \"type\": \"text\"}], \"role\": \"user\"}], \"model\": \"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001\", \"stop\": null, \"temperature\": 1.0, \"top_k\": null, \"top_p\": null}", "value": {"model": "claude-haiku-4-5-20251001", "id": "msg_011eE4nhd2EGJzPNVso7QxnP", "type": "message", "role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "I'm ready to help you search through your codebase! I'm Claude Code, Anthropic's official CLI for Claude, and I specialize in file navigation and code searching.\n\nHere's what I can do for you:\n\n- **Glob**: Find files using pattern matching (e.g., `*.py`, `src/**/*.js`)\n- **Grep**: Search file contents with regex patterns\n- **Read**: View the contents of specific files\n- **Bash**: Perform file operations like listing directories\n\nI can see you're in a git repository at `/code` on the `branch_1` branch. The repo appears clean with recent commits including \"Stuff\", \"app.py commit\", \"add some cool data\", and an initial commit.\n\nWhat would you like me to search for or explore in your codebase? Just let me know:\n- A specific file or pattern\n- Text or code you're looking for\n- Files of a certain type\n- Or any other navigation task\n\nI'm ready when you are!"}], "stop_reason": "end_turn", "stop_sequence": null, "usage": {"input_tokens": 495, "cache_creation_input_tokens": 0, "cache_read_input_tokens": 0, "cache_creation": {"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens": 0, "ephemeral_1h_input_tokens": 0}, "output_tokens": 225, "service_tier": "standard"}}}
